		<item>
		<title>Who are these PPL?: Five questions, #6</title>
		<link>http://theppl.us/blog/556</link>
		<comments>http://theppl.us/blog/556#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Fri, 09 Mar 2012 00:01:04 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>lila</dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Blog]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Five Questions]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://theppl.us/?p=556</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[Matt Tyndall meets the blog. We say enchantee, Monsieur Tyndall.]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><em>The PPL is diverse, by definition: we are bloggers, photojournalists, artists and entrepreneurs of varied ages and backgrounds committed to supporting independent media during the 2012 DNC. But let’s get a little more specific.</em></p>
<p><em>So who are these PPL, anyway? In this five-question series, you’ll get the quick-and-dirty on the folks making this thing happen.</em></p>
<p><strong><a href="http://theppl.us/556/matt" rel="attachment wp-att-557"><img class="alignleft size-medium wp-image-557" title="matt" src="http://theppl.us/wp-content/uploads/2012/03/matt-300x229.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="229" /></a>Name?</strong></p>
<p>Matthew Tyndall.</p>
<p><strong>Years in CLT?</strong></p>
<p>Been here since 2005, before that I live in Fayetteville.</p>
<p><strong>Claim to fame?</strong></p>
<p>Started <a href="http://cltblog.com" target="_blank">CLT Blog</a> in 2008 and founded <a href="http://pricelessmisc.com/" target="_blank">Priceless Miscellaneous</a> (a local creative studio).</p>
<div>
<p><strong>What are you looking forward to at the DNC?</strong></p>
</div>
<p>I love that Charlotte will get its chance to be at the forefront of national media and that we&#8217;ll get to play an active role in the national discourse. This is going to be a year where the individual voice will play a big part in deciding who our next President will be, and it is great that we will be part of that movement.</p>
<p><strong>Why are you part of the PPL?</strong></p>
<p>We are entering an era we the average citizen is the mass media. The PPL will be the best example to date of bloggers and independent media &#8212; people like you and me &#8212; being able to tell their story, and that story being broadcast to the masses. Being that nexus of information and helping others tell their story is what makes me most excited about the PPL.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
