		<title>Who are these PPL?: Five questions, #4</title>
		<link>http://theppl.us/blog/444</link>
		<comments>http://theppl.us/blog/444#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Mon, 05 Mar 2012 19:43:52 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>lila</dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Blog]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Five Questions]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://theppl.us/?p=444</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[Digital diva and space-lady extraordinaire Desiree Kane says hello.]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><em>The PPL is diverse, by definition: we are bloggers, photojournalists, artists and entrepreneurs of varied ages and backgrounds committed to supporting independent media during the 2012 DNC. But let’s get a little more specific.</em></p>
<p><em>So who are these PPL, anyway? In this five-question series, you’ll get the quick-and-dirty on the folks making this thing happen.</em></p>
<p><strong><a href="http://theppl.us/blog/444/2012-04-30-18-24-34" rel="attachment wp-att-2987"><img class="size-medium wp-image-2987 alignleft" title="2012-04-30 18.24.34" src="http://theppl.us/wp-content/uploads/2012/03/2012-04-30-18.24.34-300x225.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="225" /></a>Name?</strong></p>
<p><strong></strong>Desiree Kane.</p>
<p><strong>Years in Charlotte?</strong></p>
<p>Seven</p>
<p><strong>Claim to fame?</strong></p>
<p>Being an unofficial Charlotte cheerleader &#8212; and I&#8217;ve been to space! Okay, not literally. But I am part of the #NASATweetup press corps, which means when the last shuttle (ever) launched, I was there at the countdown clock! I&#8217;m recently back from an amazing around-the-world trip that included visits to: Doha, Qatar (for TEDxSummit), Nevada/Utah/Arizona, Hong Kong (for TEDxLionRock) and Macau!</p>
<p>Back in 2010, I orchestrated the #DNC2012 hashtag party on<a href="http://cltblog.com" target="_blank"> CLT Blog</a> to attract the touring committee to our fair city, too. More formally, I am a Guilford College grad, serve on the Steering Committee of TEDxCharlotte, sit on the Knight Foundation Community Advisory board, am a <a href="http://www.charlotteviewpoint.org" target="_blank">Charlotte Viewpoint</a> opinion columnist, sit on the Charlotte Chamber of Commerce&#8217;s entrepreneur advisory board, and am Creative Loafing Charlotte&#8217;s resident travel and tech blogger at <a href="http://clclt.com/blogs/wayfaringtechnomad">The Wayfaring Tech Nomad.</a></p>
<p><strong>What are you looking forward to at the DNC?</strong></p>
<p><strong></strong>I am looking forward to it all, especially the out-of-town visitors. I have never met a stranger and love meeting new people! The chance to show off Charlotte to these folks is just tremendous and that is SO EXCITING!!!!</p>
<p><strong>Why are you a part of the PPL?</strong></p>
<p><strong></strong>I have been to a lot of different countries and have seen that there are so many ways to live in this world. I firmly believe in paying it forward, and I feel that providing access to information, people and services that are otherwise unavailable to the unaccredited masses pays the favor forward to our society. New and traditional media with apolitical, multipartisan integrity is at the very core of an informed, engaged community we can all feel good about being a part of.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
